summary:
“Why do you keep rubbing your cheek, boy?”
Snufkin jumped, turning sharply to face his father. He had moved from his spot on the...
body:
“Why do you keep rubbing your cheek, boy?”

Snufkin jumped, turning sharply to face his father. He had moved from his spot on the couch but Snufkin didn’t even hear him. Not that he ever could.

“I-I-“ Snufkin grimaced at his stumbling. Joxter hated it when he did that. Said it made him sound weak. Joxter narrowed his eyes. “Speak, boy.” The threat beneath his words rang clear. Snufkin swallowed.

“M-my tooth hurts.”

Joxter arched a brow. “Oh?”

Snufkin nodded, rubbing at his cheek. Perhaps he shouldn’t have eaten so many treats before he left his mother’s home….

“Open your mouth.”

Snufkin blinked. “Huh?”

Joxter pulled out the chair next to Snufkin and sat down. He looked at Snufkin expectantly. Snufkin hesitated.

“P-Papa-“

“Do I need to repeat myself? You know how much I loathe that, Snufkin.”

Snufkin clamped his mouth shut, biting his lip. Those cold, dead eyes continued to stare at him, almost as if bored. But Snufkin knew better. He could see his father’s fingers twitching, waiting for Snufkin to mess up. So the boy hastily opened his mouth.

Joxter let out a small hum, clearly pleased. He reached out, clawed fingers entering Snufkin’s mouth and probing. Snufkin’s eye twitched. He clutched the fabric of his pants tightly every time a claw grazed the skin of his cheek. Oh, he dearly wanted this to be over.

Snufkin jumped when Joxter tapped a finger against his aching tooth. “Ah, I see the problem. Just a simple cavity,” Joxter explained, the pads of his fingers caressing Snufkin’s tongue. Snufkin shivered and inhaled sharply. The fingers remained in his mouth, just idly stroking. Drool began to leak out the corners of his mouth, making Snufkin cringe at the mess. Joxter’s fingers curled, choking Snufkin and making him gag.

“I’ll tear it out for you.”

Snufkin’s eyes widened. “Wh-“

Then suddenly those fingers were grabbing his tooth, yanking and yanking until-

Snufkin let out a shrill scream, blood and saliva dripping from his mouth as he scrambled away from his father. He gagged and sobbed, the pain unbearable. He turned his teary eyes towards Joxter who was simply examining the bloodied tooth. He turned toward Snufkin with a sharp smile.

“Now what do you say, Snufkin?”

The boy trembled, an absolute mess and still clutching his mouth.

“T-thank you….”

summary: Joxter shook his head, leisurely leaning against the tree. “This is your fault you know,” he said, head tilting up towards the...
body:
Joxter shook his head, leisurely leaning against the tree. “This is your fault you know,” he said, head tilting up towards the grey sky. However his words could not be heard amongst the bitter wind and the sobs of his son.

“Papa, please!” Snufkin sobbed, one hand clawing at the snow and the other stained with blood as it grasped his injured leg. “I’m sorry, I’m sorry, I won’t do it again!”

Joxter smiled, yellow fangs sharp and deadly. “Oh, but how do I know that? After all I do for you, you’re just going to run away from your dear father?” Joxter mocked, taking a step forwards towards the wounded boy. Snufkin sniffled, snot smeared across his face. “Papa, please. I love you, I’m sorry. Don’t leave me here,” he begged, his hand trying to reach for Joxter’s boot.

Joxter cooed at the pitiful sight of his son. “I’m sure an hour out here will suffice,” he said, grinning wickedly at his son’s wail.

“Papa, no! Please! I’ll die out here!”

Joxter kicked his hand away and shoved his hands in his pockets. “Then you shouldn’t have ran from me.”

Snufkin’s sobs and pleads echoed throughout the woods, following Joxter as he made his way back home.
